Enum AriaDropEffect

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<AriaDropEffect>
      • net.sf.mmm.client.ui.api.aria.datatype.AriaDropEffect
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<AriaDropEffect>, AttributeReadValue<String>, Datatype, EnumType<String>, SimpleDatatype<String>

    public enum AriaDropEffect
extends Enum<AriaDropEffect>
implements EnumType<String>
    This enum contains the possible values for AttributeReadAriaDropEffect.getDropEffect().
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      COPY
      Indicating that a duplicate of the source object will be dropped into the target.
      COPY_EXECUTE
      Indicates the combination of COPY and EXECUTE.
      EXECUTE
      Indicating that a function supported by the drop target is executed, using the drag source as an input.
      LINK
      Indicating that a reference or shortcut to the dragged object will be created in the target object.
      LINK_EXECUTE
      Indicates the combination of LINK and EXECUTE.
      MOVE
      Indicating that the source object will be removed from its current location and dropped into the target.
      MOVE_EXECUTE
      Indicates the combination of LINK and EXECUTE.
      NONE
      Indicating that no operation can be performed.
      POPUP
      Indicating that a popup menu or dialog allows the user to choose one of the drag operations (copy, move, link, execute) and any other drag functionality, such as cancel.
